# Skill authoring

## Frontmatter description

In `SKILL.md` frontmatter, write `description` as a plain 1-2 lines string include minimal usage example.
Never use YAML block scalars (`>`, `|`, `>-`, `|-`, or variants).

Good:

```yaml
description: Create or update a GitHub pull request title and body from the current branch. Use when opening or updating a pull request.
```

Bad:

```yaml
description: >
  Routes GitHub pull request work to the right PR skill.
  Use when opening or updating a pull request.
```

## Self-contained

Keep each skill self-contained.
Do not pull in or duplicate guidance from other skills unless the user asks to reference or align with another skill.
The same applies when the skill already references other skills and you are extending that linkage.

Do not add provenance or mirroring labels on skill content.
Write the rules directly, do not prefix sections with where they came from.

Bad: `Core rules (mirrored from other-skill)`

Reference other skills by name only, in backticks: `skill-name-here`.
Do not use file paths (e.g. `.cursor/skills/other-skill/SKILL.md`, `reference.md`).

When the skill lives in a repo, do not reference personal global skills.
The repo and other team members may not have the same global skills you do.
Only reference skills that ship with that repo.

## Numbered steps

Use `1.`, `2.`, ... only for short sequences where each item fits on one line.

When there are too many points, or a single numbered item wraps onto multiple lines, break the sequence into headings instead.
Use `### Step 1 - Short summary` and so on.
Put detail in paragraphs under each heading.

Good:

```markdown
### Step 1

Confirm scope with the user.
Stop and wait for a reply before continuing.

### Step 2

Write `plan.md` from the confirmed scope.
```

Bad:

```markdown
1. Confirm scope with the user. Stop and wait for a reply before continuing.
2. Write `plan.md` from the confirmed scope.
3. Implement only after the user approves the plan.
4. Run the quality gate before finishing.
5. Update `plan.md` if decisions change during implementation.
```
